### API Tests for Mixed Architecture (JPA + gRPC)
### Same-DB: Status & Category use @ManyToOne (JPA/SQL FK)
### Cross-DB: Worker uses Integer ID (gRPC validation)

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### ============================================
### SETUP: Create Required Entities First
### ============================================

### 1. Create Task Status (taskdb - JPA managed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/statuses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "statusName": "In Progress"
}

### 2. Create another Status
POST {{baseUrl}}/statuses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "statusName": "Completed"
}

### 3. Create Task Category (taskdb - JPA managed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryName": "Development"
}

### 4. Create another Category
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryName": "Testing"
}

### 5. Create Worker (workerdb - separate database)
POST {{baseUrl}}/workers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workerName": "John",
  "workerLastName": "Doe"
}

### 6. Create another Worker
POST {{baseUrl}}/workers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workerName": "Jane",
  "workerLastName": "Smith"
}

### ============================================
### TASK OPERATIONS (Mixed Validation)
### ============================================

### 7. Create Task (gRPC for Worker, JPA for Status/Category)
### Console shows: ✓ gRPC: Worker validated + ✓ JPA: Status/Category validated
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Complete OOSD Project",
  "description": "Implement REST and gRPC with mixed architecture",
  "workerId": 1,
  "status": {
    "statusId": 1
  },
  "category": {
    "categoryId": 1
  }
}

### 8. Create another Task
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Write Documentation",
  "description": "Document the mixed JPA+gRPC approach",
  "workerId": 2,
  "status": {
    "statusId": 1
  },
  "category": {
    "categoryId": 1
  }
}

### 9. Get All Tasks
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks

### 10. Get Task by ID (includes Status and Category objects via JPA)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks/1

### 11. Update Task (validates via gRPC and JPA)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tasks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Complete OOSD Project - UPDATED",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "workerId": 1,
  "status": {
    "statusId": 2
  },
  "category": {
    "categoryId": 1
  }
}

### 12. Delete Task
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tasks/1

### ============================================
### VALIDATION TESTS (Should Fail with 400)
### ============================================

### 13. Invalid Worker ID (gRPC validation fails)
### Expected: "Worker with id 999 not found via gRPC"
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Invalid Task",
  "workerId": 999,
  "status": {
    "statusId": 1
  },
  "category": {
    "categoryId": 1
  }
}

### 14. Invalid Status ID (JPA validation fails)
### Expected: "Status with id 999 not found"
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Invalid Task",
  "workerId": 1,
  "status": {
    "statusId": 999
  },
  "category": {
    "categoryId": 1
  }
}

### 15. Invalid Category ID (JPA validation fails)
### Expected: "Category with id 999 not found"
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Invalid Task",
  "workerId": 1,
  "status": {
    "statusId": 1
  },
  "category": {
    "categoryId": 999
  }
}

### ============================================
### WORKER OPERATIONS (workerdb)
### ============================================

### 16. Get All Workers
GET {{baseUrl}}/workers

### 17. Get Worker by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/workers/1

### 18. Update Worker
PUT {{baseUrl}}/workers/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workerName": "John Updated",
  "workerLastName": "Doe Updated"
}

### 19. Delete Worker (checks for assigned tasks via gRPC)
### Console: ⚠ gRPC: Worker has X assigned task(s)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/workers/2

### ============================================
### STATUS OPERATIONS (taskdb - JPA managed)
### ============================================

### 20. Get All Statuses
GET {{baseUrl}}/statuses

### 21. Get Status by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/statuses/1

### 22. Update Status
PUT {{baseUrl}}/statuses/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "statusName": "In Progress - Updated"
}

### 23. Delete Status
### Note: May fail due to SQL FK constraint if tasks reference it!
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/statuses/2

### ============================================
### CATEGORY OPERATIONS (taskdb - JPA managed)
### ============================================

### 24. Get All Categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories

### 25. Get Category by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/1

### 26. Create Category
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "categoryName": "Bug Fix"
}

### 27. Delete Category
### Note: May fail due to SQL FK constraint if tasks reference it!
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/categories/2

### ============================================
### USER INFO OPERATIONS (workerdb)
### ============================================

### 28. Create User
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "admin",
  "password": "password123",
  "mail": "admin@example.com"
}

### 29. Get All Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

### 30. Get User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/1

### 31. Update User
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "admin_updated",
  "password": "newpassword456",
  "mail": "admin_updated@example.com"
}

### 32. Delete User
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/1


